tablr.column

Class Column

  • java.lang.Object
    • tablr.column.Column
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanColumn, EmailColumn, IntegerColumn, StringColumn

    public abstract class Column
extends java.lang.Object
    Responsibility:
    Holding the cells of a column.
    Invariants:
  • The default value of a column is always effective.
        defaultValue != null
  • The list of values is always effective.
        values != null
  • The name of the column is always effective
        name != null

    • Constructor Detail

      • Column

        @Model
protected Column(java.lang.String name,
                         int nbOfValues,
                         java.lang.String defaultValue,
                         boolean blanksAllowed)
                  throws IllegalColumnException,
                         java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initialize this new column with given name, given number of values, given default value and given blanks allowed.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the new column.
        nbOfValues - The number of values of the new column.
        defaultValue - The default value of the new column
        blanksAllowed - Boolean to determine whether blanks are allowed or not.
        Effects:
      • The name of the new column is set to the given name.
            setName(name)
      • Variable blanksAllowed registering whether blanks are allowed or not is set to the given parameter for blanks allowed or not.
            setBlanksAllowed(blanksAllowed)
      • The default value of the new column is set to the given default value.
            setDefaultValue(defaultValue)
      • There are nbOfValues new values created in the list values, with as value the given default value.
            for each I in 1..nbOfValues
              addValue(getDefaultValue())
        • Throws:
        IllegalColumnException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException

      • addValueAt

        public void addValueAt(int index,
                       java.lang.String value)
                throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Add the given value as a value for this column at the given index
        Parameters:
        index - The index at which the new value should be added.
        value - The value to be added.
        Postconditions:
      • This column has the given value as one of its values at the given index
            new.getValueAt(index) == value
      • The number of values for this column is incremented by 1.
            new.getNbValues() == getNbValues() + 1
      • All the values of this column at an index exceeding the given index, are registered as a value on an index one higher than the previous one.
            for each I in 1..getNbValues():
              (new.getValueAt(I + 1) == getValueAt(I)
        • Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - The given value cannot be a value of this column at the given index. | ! canHaveAsValueAt(index, value)
